&lt;h1 id="nyust-interview-reflection"&gt;NYUST Interview Reflection&lt;a href="#nyust-interview-reflection" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Link to this section"&gt;&lt;svg class="h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"&gt;&lt;g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"&gt;&lt;path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/&gt;&lt;path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Three familiar professors greeted me: TWC, CMW, and LSL.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>My First Triathlon: Graduation Is Not the End, But a New Beginning</title><link>https://ezrawu-tw.github.io/en/posts/my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning/</link><pubDate>Sat, 16 Aug 2025 14:22:14 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ezrawu-tw.github.io/en/posts/my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;slug: My-First-Triathlon-Graduation-Is-Not-the-End-But-a-New-Beginning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id="-my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning"&gt;🏅 My First Triathlon: Graduation Is Not the End, But a New Beginning&lt;a href="#-my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Link to this section"&gt;&lt;svg class="h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"&gt;&lt;g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"&gt;&lt;path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/&gt;&lt;path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;by Ezra Wu | Jul 4, 2025&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That was a &lt;strong&gt;1 hour and 40 minutes&lt;/strong&gt; challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I participated in a triathlon for the first time in my life—running and rafting—on a hilly course. Halfway through, my body refused to cooperate, leaving only my willpower to push me forward.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Coolest Thing I've Ever Done</title><link>https://ezrawu-tw.github.io/en/posts/the-coolest-thing-i-ve-ever-done/</link><pubDate>Sat, 16 Aug 2025 14:11:41 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ezrawu-tw.github.io/en/posts/the-coolest-thing-i-ve-ever-done/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;slug: The-Coolest-Thing-I-ve-Ever-Done&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id="the-coolest-thing-ive-ever-done-building-an-ai-learning-tool-for-visually-impaired-children"&gt;The Coolest Thing I&amp;rsquo;ve Ever Done: Building an AI Learning Tool for Visually Impaired Children&lt;a href="#the-coolest-thing-ive-ever-done-building-an-ai-learning-tool-for-visually-impaired-children" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Link to this section"&gt;&lt;svg class="h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"&gt;&lt;g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"&gt;&lt;path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/&gt;&lt;path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;By Ezra Wu | April 5, 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="the-beginning-a-spark-of-an-idea"&gt;The Beginning: A Spark of an Idea&lt;a href="#the-beginning-a-spark-of-an-idea" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Link to this section"&gt;&lt;svg class="h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"&gt;&lt;g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"&gt;&lt;path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/&gt;&lt;path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;In October 2024, I saw the announcement for the &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Imagine Cup&lt;/strong&gt;. A thought flashed through my mind: &lt;em&gt;What if we could really use technology to change the world?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Birth of Our Metaverse English Club</title><link>https://ezrawu-tw.github.io/en/posts/the-birth-of-our-metaverse-english-club/</link><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ezrawu-tw.github.io/en/posts/the-birth-of-our-metaverse-english-club/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;slug: The-Birth-of-Our-Metaverse-English-Club&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 2024, I co-founded a club that quickly became one of my favorite projects: the &lt;strong&gt;Metaverse English Research Club&lt;/strong&gt;. What makes this club special is its commitment to creating a fun, interactive, and immersive learning environment. We wanted to break the fear often associated with learning English, replacing it with curiosity and joy.&lt;/p&gt;
